Ignatius had monitored the situation when he scanned others aproaching.
&quot;Ignatius to Slayer, new plan, fall back and wait for further contact.&quot; The
Trainers were in over thier heads but were in to deep to up and run. He knew
that in battle sooner or later there would be injured bots. That one fact
was to good a chance to pass up.

He started gathering his equipment when a shadow passed over him. He turned
to see another dragon staring down at him. His scans of the cave must have
been reflected around this bot by the ice formations.

&quot;I couldn&#39;t help overhearing your conversations, You know that I can&#39;t allow
that.&quot; Necromancer stared down at the Trainer, his teeth glareing,
reflecting the smaller bots fear. The elemental stood up on his back legs
brandishing the maximal symbol on his chest. &quot;ROARRRRRRRRRRRRR&quot;

The force of the roar forced Ignatius off the cliff sending him tumbling
downward. He quickly righted himself by transforming to eagle mode and
attempting to fly away. Necromancer quickly blocked his escape and
redirected the eagle back toward the CF. The Trainers plan to herd a Maximal
was being reversed, now a Maximal was herding him.
